Class MotionStabilizePointKey<I extends ImageSingleBand,T extends InvertibleTransform>

  boofcv.alg.sfm.d2.ImageMotionPointKey<I,T>
      boofcv.alg.sfm.d2.MotionStabilizePointKey<I,T>

public class MotionStabilizePointKey<I extends ImageSingleBand,T extends InvertibleTransform>
extends ImageMotionPointKey<I,T>

Extension of ImageMotionPointKey specifically designed to stabilize image motion. The algorithm attempts to minimize the difference in pixel difference between the first image and the current image. If the difference between the current frame and the first frame becomes too large then the current frame becomes the new first frame.

Author:
Peter Abeles

public MotionStabilizePointKey(ImagePointTracker<I> tracker,

                               T model,
                               int thresholdKeyFrame,

                               int largeMotionThreshold)
Specify algorithms to use internally. Each of these classes must work with compatible data structures.

Parameters:
tracker - feature tracker
modelMatcher - Fits model to track data
modelRefiner - (Optional) Refines the found model using the entire inlier set. Can be null.
model - Motion model data structure
thresholdKeyFrame - If the number of inlier is less than this number the keyframe will change.
thresholdReset - If the number of inlier is less than this number a reset will occur.
largeMotionThreshold - If the transform from the key frame to the current frame is more than this a reset will occur.
